# Kconfig.batl_vcu_keyfob — Board Identity in the Kconfig Tree
#
# =============================================================================
# WHAT THIS FILE DOES
# =============================================================================
#
# This file registers your board in Zephyr's Kconfig system. When you pass
# "-b batl_vcu_keyfob" to west build, the build system defines the symbol
# BOARD_BATL_VCU_KEYFOB automatically. This file then uses 'select' to pull
# in the correct SoC configuration.
#
# The 'select' statement is a Kconfig mechanism that forces another symbol
# to be enabled. So 'select SOC_EFR32BG24A010F1024IM48' means: "when this
# board is chosen, automatically enable the SoC configuration for the
# EFR32BG24A010F1024IM48."
#
# IMPORTANT: The SOC symbol name must match what's defined in the Zephyr
# SoC Kconfig tree under zephyr/soc/silabs/. If the exact part number
# isn't defined as a Kconfig symbol, you may need to use a broader family
# symbol like SOC_EFR32BG24 or SOC_SERIES_EFR32BG24.
#
# To find available SoC Kconfig symbols, search:
#   grep -r "SOC_EFR32BG24\|SOC_SERIES_EFR32BG24" <workspace>/zephyr/soc/silabs/
# =============================================================================

config BOARD_BATL_VCU_KEYFOB
	select SOC_EFR32BG24A010F1024IM48
